<br>
Earring is good if you spend time grouping, or solo mostly indoors.  Outdoors, the horse is a better option.<br>
<br>
Jboots are some of the only methods of escape availible to mages.  They will save your life many, many times.<br>
<br>
Soloing outdoors with a Burnt Wood Staff and a Horse is a great experience.  However, while both are independantly useful, neither item lives up to its full potential without the other.  They are more of a combo.<br>
<br>
You know more about your playstyle than any other, but for me... I bought things in this order...<br>
<br>
Jboots, for escape and travel. (actually got from guildie.)<br>
BWS, for clicky nuke.<br>
Then I sold most of my gear that I had collected, because more mana did very little for me.  Its all about mana regen.<br>
Bought the cheap pony.  Vastly improved my life.<br>
Now saving for Earring and Envemoned Sleeves.  The Sleeves miserably fail the &quot;bang for the buck&quot; test, but hey, fun value. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243737"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~moghedan/pics/mogtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
