<br>
The earring's stats will only become fully useful at 51.  I do not know if the FT kicks in before that or not.  If it does, could be a good buy.  If not it can wait.<br>
<br>
Resist gear ... useless.  Yeah, it helps, but at 42 you wont need much.  At higher levels, should you need it, mages can summon the blanket which is a good one, and shard of the core.  Together thats usually enough to get you where you need to be on top of some good regualr gear.  I wouldnt go this route at all.<br>
<br>
Horse and Jboots ... these are better ideas.  Personally, Id get the horse over jboots, heres why.  Both are outdoors only.  At 51 when you can get run3, which is 30% move, it will be faster than the horse and on all the time.  JBoots is only 35% move.  Very minor upgrade there, and only outside, and only if you bother clicking it.  Makes JBoots seem like a not so good purchase down the road.<br>
<br>
Horse on the other hand, is useful for its effects even after you can move faster than it (run3 &gt; cheap horse for move).  Very useful.  In fact its the one thing you listed that will for sure help you now and later and wont get upgraded.<br>
<br>
IMO get the horse, or if you decide potc ear is better then get that.  Both will help you doing soloing, grouping, small raiding.  Potc ear will affect more of these situations than horse (raids often in dungeons where no horse usable) but horse will make more of an impact on xping. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
